3.1.2. Multicollinearity test
Multicollinearity testing can be performed if the tolerance value is less than 0.1 or the VIF value is greater than 10, which is considered multicollinearity. The multicollinearity test results in Table 2 show that all the tolerance values of the independent variables are greater than 0.1. The VIF values of the independent variables are all less than 10, which is below this number, there is no multicollinearity phenomenon.
