3.2.4. Effect of flipbook utilization (X1), learning interest (X2), learning motivation (X3) on learning outcomes (Y)
Based on Table 7, it can be seen that the calculated F is 29.967 > Ftable is 2.77 with a significance level of 0.000 < 0.005. So, the decision was made to reject Ho and accept Ha. This means that all independent variables (effect of flipbook media use, learning interest, and learning motivation) have the ability to simultaneously influence the dependent variable (learning outcomes).


